    • Method Detail

      • process

        protected void process(User sender,
                       String[] label,
                       String[] rawArguments)
        Description copied from class: ValidCommand
        This method runs the command. It goes through each argument and will process and validate it. Then, so long as that passes, it will run the command's system. Last it will clear out any saved table data and stored argument values.
        Overrides:
        process in class ValidCommand
        Parameters:
        sender - the sender of the command.
        label - the label from which the command was sent
        rawArguments - the unparsed and non-validated arguments.

      • processTabComplete

        public List<String> processTabComplete(User sender,
                                       String[] rawArguments)
        Description copied from class: ValidCommand
        Process the tab complete for the given command. This also takes into account the fact the last argument provided is what is supposed to be changed. The arguments passed include only the arguments for the command, and not the actual label used. The raw arguments passed should always have at least a length of 1.
        Overrides:
        processTabComplete in class ValidCommand
        Parameters:
        sender - the person who sent the tab request.
        rawArguments - the arguments already typed by the player.
        Returns:
        the suggestions for tab complete.

      • getSubCommandNames

        public List<String> getSubCommandNames(User sender,
                                       String start)
        Get the name all sub commands whose name or one if it's aliases starts with the given string. The name for each command will be whichever piece was provided, whether that be the alias or the name.
        Parameters:
        sender - the person trying to access the sub commands.
        start - the beginning of the label.
        Returns:
        the command labels if any are found.

      • getSubCommands

        public List<ValidCommand> getSubCommands()
        Get a view of all the sub commands. This is not able to be modified and doing so will throw an exception.
        Returns:
        all the sub commands.

      • validRun

        public void validRun(User sender,
                     String[] label,
                     List<CommandArgument<?>> arguments)
        Description copied from class: ValidCommand
        Runs the command after all processing has already been completed. The label is an array of the label used by this command as well as any parent command. The arguments will always be there, whether they are used or not. To check if optional arguments were used, call the method CommandArgument.hasValue().
        Specified by:
        validRun in class ValidCommand
        Parameters:
        sender - the sender of the command.
        label - the label of the command.
        arguments - the arguments of the command.
